---
const faqs = [
  {
    id: 'expertise-1',
    name: 'Do you work with all types of creators and platforms?',
    description:
      'Yes. We adapt our workflow to any creator and any platform where content is published. Our strongest experience is with YouTube, where we’ve developed scalable creative and production systems — but our services are not limited to it.'
  },
  {
    id: 'expertise-2',
    name: 'What’s included in the Inspirational Report?',
    description:
     'You receive tailored ideations built specifically for your tone, narrative, goals, and vertical. Each delivery includes one core idea expanded into multiple creative variants, trend-aware angles, and clear filming or execution priorities.'  },
  {
    id: 'expertise-3',
    name: 'What’s included in the Editing service?',
    description:
      'Editing for Shorts, long-form videos, repurposed content (shorts extracted from long videos), or fully intentional vertical content designed from scratch. We also offer optional premium enhancements such as CGI and VFX depending on your plan.',
  },
  {
    id: 'expertise-4',
    name: 'How do I send footage for editing?',
    description:
      'Through any cloud service you prefer — Google Drive, Dropbox, WeTransfer, Mega, or your current storage workflow. We adapt to your existing process.',
  },
  {
    id: 'expertise-5',
    name: 'Are there limits on video length or file size?',
    description:
      'Each plan includes a monthly allocation of editable minutes and suggested file volume to ensure a smooth workflow. If you need to send more content, we simply coordinate a plan upgrade or a one-time add-on. Nothing is blocked automatically — everything is aligned with you first.',
  },
  {
    id: 'expertise-6',
    name: 'Do you use AI for ideation or editing?',
    description:
      'No. All Inspirational Reports are created entirely by a human team specializing in scripting, narrative design, trend analysis, and copywriting. Editing is also performed exclusively by professional editors. AI may be used only as a supporting tool for minor tasks (e.g., transcription or cleanup), but creative direction and editing are never AI-generated.',
  },
  {
    id: 'expertise-7',
    name: 'Can I cancel anytime?',
    description:
      'Yes. When you cancel, your service remains active until the exact end date of the billing period you’ve already paid for. It does not renew for an additional month.',
  },
  {
    id: 'expertise-8',
    name: 'Do you offer refunds?',
    description:
      'Due to the nature of creative work, refunds are not offered. However, you can cancel at any time and keep access to the service until the end of your current billing cycle.',
  },
  {
    id: 'expertise-9',
    name: 'What are the delivery times?',
    // Usa backticks aquí:
    description: `Delivery times depend on the service:
Inspirational Report
Delivered according to the frequency of your plan (e.g., weekly).

Shorts Editing
Typically 24–72 hours, depending on volume and complexity.

Long-Form Editing
Time varies based on length and difficulty:
Simple videos (5–12 min): 3–5 business days`,
  },

];
---

<section class="py-16 sm:py-20">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Faqs</h2>
      <div class="lg:col-span-2">
        <dl
          class="-mt-3"
          x-data="{ selected: null, toggle(value) { this.selected = this.selected === value ? null : value } }"
        >
          {
            faqs.map((feature, index) => (
              <div
                class="rounded-3xl px-4 transition"
                x-data={`{ id: ${index}, get isOpen() { return this.id === this.selected }, get isNextOpen() { return (this.id + 1) === this.selected } }`}
                x-bind:class="{ 'bg-primary-500/10 dark:bg-primary-400/10': isOpen }"
              >
                <dt
                  class="border-b text-lg transition"
                  x-cloak
                  x-bind:class="{ 'border-transparent': isOpen || isNextOpen, 'border-primary-900/10 dark:border-primary-300/10': !(isOpen || isNextOpen) }"
                >
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="group block w-full py-6 text-left transition focus-visible:outline-none"
                    aria-controls={feature.id}
                    x-on:click="toggle(id)"
                    aria-expanded="false"
                    x-bind:aria-expanded="isOpen.toString()"
                  >
                    <div class="group-focus-visible:outline-primary-950 dark:group-focus-visible:outline-primary-200 flex items-center justify-between rounded-3xl group-focus-visible:outline group-focus-visible:outline-2 group-focus-visible:outline-offset-2">
                      <span class="font-medium">{feature.name}</span>
                      <span class="ml-6 flex h-7 items-center">
                        <svg
                          class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 h-6 w-6 rotate-0 transform transition duration-200 ease-in-out"
                          x-bind:class="{ '-rotate-180': isOpen, 'rotate-0': !isOpen }"
                          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                          fill="currentColor"
                          aria-hidden="true"
                        >
                          <path d="M11.9997 13.1714L16.9495 8.22168L18.3637 9.63589L11.9997 15.9999L5.63574 9.63589L7.04996 8.22168L11.9997 13.1714Z" />
                        </svg>
                      </span>
                    </div>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd class="pb-6 pr-6" id={feature.id} x-show="isOpen" x-cloak x-collapse>
                  <p class="text-primary-950/70 dark:text-primary-200/70 text-base">
                    {feature.description}
                  </p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
